page.title: 20SUMMARY
page.content: The area was covered by two schools: Flash Ley Middle School,an urban school from the Rising Brook area of Stafford about 4km from Milford. The 11 year old (2nd year)pupils were all involved,but editing was by: Pages1&20,Mr.A.Fryer,Pgs2&3 J.Rowley S. Subramanian,H. Finney & E.Shaw.Pg4 J. Garbett & P.Hanlon.Pg5 S.Gibbs, S.Barnsley,Pg6 R.Greenwood & J.Osborne. Pg7 S.Subramanian Pg8 J.Rowley & G.Price. Pg9 P.Bailey Pg10 P.Hanlon. Pg11 A.Northwood. Pg12 T.Banks Pg13 M.Pownall St.John's Junior R.C.School in Great Haywood acted as support school.The top juniors(11yrs)completed the following: Pg14 E.Featherstone. Pg15 A.Mellows. Pg16 E.Hobbs.
